&lt;p&gt;Please note that interviews for this post will take place overMICROSOFT TEAMSonMonday 23rd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job function:Vasectomy Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Description:SessionalVasectomy Registered NurseorMidwife (Vasectomy Practitioner)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered Nurses should refer to the &quot;Registered Nurse&quot; Job specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered Midwives should refer to the &quot;Vasectomy Practitioner&quot; Job specification (under Additional Information).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Gillingham, Medway&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift pattern: 1-3 Tuesdays per month (depending on demand for Vasectomy in the local area)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About Us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Stopes UK is a reproductive health charity, best known for its abortion services which help 70,000 women a year. Our network of welcoming clinics and local community services, together with a24-hourconfidential helpline work, provide high quality, safe, accessible and compassionate advice, care and support for the women and men who need us. 95% of our services are commissioned by the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our clinic network is growing as part of our strategy to be the charity of choice for the women and men who turn to us for help, and for our funders. Our influence is growing too, as we work to increase public and political understanding of the issues women and men face in making reproductive choices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for people who share our drive to provide the best quality care to everyone who needs our services to join our committed teams of clinical, management and support staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re proud to be champions for reproductive choice. Marie Stopes International works in 37 countries around the world to help women and girls to havechildrenbychoice,notchance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About the role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Nurse / Midwife at Marie Stopes, you can expect to work in a busy and fast-paced environment, providing excellent clinical care and guidance to our vasectomy clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Supporting surgeon/client during procedure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Liaising with vas admin team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Assisting with admitting/discharging clients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Ensuring client is recovering well&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Post operative issues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive £19.56 per hour for your hard work and commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rewarding role and would suit someone who enjoys working autonomously and in a fast-paced environment. You will be passionate about providing excellent care and have a keen interest in sexual and reproductive healthcare. In addition to this, you will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Post-registration experience of working in a fast paced, high activity environment to time-slotted appointments i.e. A&amp;E, theatre, acute, labour ward, outpatients or work experience as a practise nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, both verbal and written&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- The ability to work in a close team and enjoy supporting colleagues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- It is essential that you are flexible&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work for Marie Stopes UK,you must be pro-choice on abortion and an advocate of our mission of &#39;children by choice, not chance&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more details, please see the attached job framework.&lt;/p&gt;
